<TEXT>
a college basketball star expected to be 
chosen in the first round of the professional draft died sunday 
after collapsing during a tournament game 
hank gathers 23 crumpled to the court moments after sinking a 
thunderous slam dunk for loyola marymount university in a west 
coast conference tournament game against portland 
he appeared to suffer convulsions for a few seconds while his 
mother and sister rushed out the stands in front of a hushed crowd 
at gersten pavilion their cries were audible to everyone in the 
building 
he was taken to daniel freeman marina hospital where he was 
pronounced dead 
cardiologist mason weiss told a news conference the cause of 
death was unknown and an autopsy would be performed 
gathers was given medication after a similar collapse during a 
game dec 9 and doctors said at the time they believed the problem 
was an accelerated heartbeat 
gathers was one of only two players in division i of the 
national collegiate athletic association to lead the nation in 
scoring and rebounding in the same season as a junior last season 
gathers averaged 327 points and 137 rebounds joining xavier 
mcdaniel of wichita state in 198485 as the only ncaa player to 
lead the nation in both categories 
his 1015 points last season ranked him 11th on the alltime 
singleseason scoring list 
a 6foot7 210pound center from philadelphia gathers was 
expected to be a firstround selection in this years national 
basketball association draft 
the game was cancelled with marymounts lions leading portland 
2513 in the first half the rest of the tournament also was 
postponed 
it all happened so fast portland coach larry steele said 
after sending his players back to the teams hotel within two 
seconds everybody realized thathank needed help right now were 
not even having a thought 
gathers and teammate bo kimble lead the nation in scoring this 
season 
</TEXT>
