<TEXT>
military personnel flying on official duty have 
been barred from using hawaiian airlines the department of defense 
announced 
discrepancies in the airlines maintenance practices and 
documentation caused the ruling pentagon officials said 
the action was taken feb 23 following a scheduled weeklong 
maintenance inspection by the defense department 
the company is meeting with the military airlift command and 
intends to resume mac charters in the near future hawaiian 
airline spokesman keoni wagner said friday 
the carrier has been serving the military since 1963 
the discrepancies found during the weeklong visit concerned 
maintenance practices procedures and documentation which were 
being done improperly or not at all according to a statement 
issued through the air force military airlift command office at 
hickam air force base 
the order bars the carrier from serving individual military 
personnel on commercial flights or from flying charter flights for 
military maneuvers 
</TEXT>
