<TEXT>
hunters may be called in to kill some of 
the 20 bison that wandered out of yellowstone national park late 
last week state wildlife officials said saturday 
park bison are thought to carry the disease brucellosis which 
can cause spontaneous abortion in cattle 
the animals were spotted by a game warden thursday night grazing 
outside the parks west boundary said john cada of the state 
department of fish wildlife and parks 
a hunt is likely if the bison get in a position where we can 
take some cada told the associated press we may take a few to 
encourage the others to return to the park 
state law allows the controlled hunting of bison that enter 
montana from the national park 
the policy has aroused the wrath of animalrights groups which 
objected when the state allowed hunters to kill 569 bison last 
winter 
</TEXT>
