<DOCNO> AP900304-0010 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
an important witness went into the wind 
apparently skipping town and carrying with him a key part of the 
prosecutions case against six white men charged with murdering a 
black teenager 
john vento admitted participating in the aug 23 racial attack 
on yusuf hawkins and agreed to testify for the prosecution but he 
disappeared in december 
jury selection in the case was to start monday brooklyn 
district attorney charles j hynes said he would seek a onemonth 
adjournment unless the 21yearold highschool dropout surfaces 
on saturday meanwhile about 300 people led by hawkins father 
marched to ventos home in the mainly white bensonhurst 
neighborhood of brooklyn to protest prosectors handling of the 
case 
it seems that this case has never been taken seriously by the 
district attorneys office said the rev al sharpton a march 
organizer 
police on motorcycles and wearing riot gear separated the 
marchers who arrived in six buses about 230 pm from 
bensonhurst residents 
everything was peaceful said officer ralph st just a 
police spokesman he reported no arrests 
former district attorney elizabeth holtzman had struck a deal to 
drop charges against vento if he would testify 
hynes who took office in january maintains the loss of ventos 
testimony would not be devastating but privately prosecutors say 
the case is improved immeasurably with ventos participation 
without him is it hopeless the opinion is divided said 
one source in the prosecutors office who spoke on condition that 
he not be identified 
lawyers for the defendants say even if vento reappears hynes 
has suffered a major setback 
vento is going to be a lowlife with no credibility defense 
lawyer stephen murphy said 
vento was a member of a gang of some 30 young whites many of 
them wielding baseball bats who surrounded the 16yearold 
hawkins and three of his friends on a street in the mainly white 
bensonhurst neighborhood 
the gang had assembled out of a mistaken belief that a group of 
blacks and hispanics were about to enter their enclave to attend a 
neighborhood girls birthday party and create trouble police said 
the whites set upon hawkins and his pals who had come to look at a 
used car for sale 
joseph fama 19 is charged with fatally shooting hawkins in the 
chest five other whites also have been charged in the killing and 
a seventh is charged with assault only fama is being held without 
bail 
hynes said vento went into the wind around christmas 
authorities do not believe he met with foul play instead hynes 
believes vento chickened out when faced with the prospect of 
testifying against his friends 
in announcing ventos disappearance last week prosecutors tried 
to lure him back saying that if he breaks his promise to testify 
they have sufficient evidence to charge him with seconddegree 
murder for his role in the attack 
murphy attorney for alleged bensonhurst ringleader keith 
mondello 20 said the credibility of a major witness who 
prosecutors admit took part in a murder and then fled after cutting 
a generous deal is nil 
the other defense lawyers agree his decision to abscond will 
probably severely undermine his credibility as a witness said 
benjamin brafman the lawyer for defendant james patino 24 
i have to assume that prosecutors believe hes going to be a 
very important witness brafman said normally when a witness 
who could be a defendant gets a complete pass that person is 
deemed extremely important by the prosecution 
stanley meyer lawyer for the accused triggerman described 
vento as an integral part of hynes case he said vento was 
expected to testify that someone put the gun in famas hands 
we dispute that meyer said the thought crosses my mind 
that maybe he doesnt want to testify because he doesnt want to 
commit perjury 
hawkins parents said thursday they felt betrayed by 
prosecutors who they said promised them there would be no deals 
with their sons attackers 
the case has reunited some of the lead characters from another 
case that grabbed the citys attention 2 years ago the howard 
beach case in which a white mob chased a black man onto a highway 
where he was killed by a car 
hynes successfully prosecuted that case and went on to be 
elected brooklyn district attorney last year succeeding holtzman 
who was elected city comptroller 
murphy a scrappy lawyer who speaks in a scream defended the 
only howard beach murder defendant who was acquitted 
</TEXT>
