<TEXT>
westmar college trustees voted 
overwhelmingly saturday to become a branch of teikyo university of 
japan a merger that westmars president called a marriage but four 
trustees protested by resigning 
more than twothirds of the 37member board approved the merger 
after a sixhour session college president arthur richardson said 
at a news conference late saturday he declined to disclose the 
actual vote count 
the agreement will bring a substantial dowry to the tiny 
centuryold college and gives tokyobased teikyo its third branch 
in the united states teikyo has nine other campuses in japan and 
branches in england and holland 
