<TEXT>
the pentagon is wasting no time offering 
answers to one of the most compelling questions raised by the 
demise of the cold war who is the enemy now 
its drug runners terrorists third world despots and even oil 
spills the pentagon brass say 
at the same time they havent dismissed entirely the threat of 
soviet attack on the west even as moscow begins pulling its troops 
out of eastern europe 
the world has entered an era of violent peace says adm 
carlisle trost the navys top officer it is a time of reduced 
odds that the superpowers will lob nuclear missiles at each others 
cities but of more frequent and more lethal conflict among rival 
third world nations he told congress recently 
the message from the pentagon is that not only is the military 
needed for its traditional mission but that military might must be 
tailored to battle exotic new threats ones not previously 
considered big risks to the future of western democracy 
its unclear how this notion will sell on capitol hill 
