in january the landmarks preservation board nominated the blue 
moon but late last month the agencys staff recommended that 
landmark status be denied the staff report agreed with hannah who 
said the tavern failed to meet structural requirements mostly 
because of remodeling in the last 25 years 
landmark status would prevent the owners from tearing down the 
tavern and any remodeling would be subject to restrictions 
the building housing blue moon was built as a garage in 1923 and 
converted into one of the citys first postprohibition taverns 11 
years later its location was close to the boundary of an area 
around the university of washington where sales of alcoholic 
beverages were banned 
inside the clacking billiard balls raucous laughter animated 
