from this tiny island off the coast of cape cod and put them into a 
book i dont know what it is but there are a lot of ghosts on 
nantucket 
one story tells of a poltergeist residing in a house built in 
1808 and once owned ominously enough by a man named william 
coffin coffin a prominent wig shop owner died embittered after 
being accused of stealing 21000 from the nantucket bank in 1795 
twentyone years after the theft a convict in a new york state 
prison confessed to the crime but years of accusations and 
