<TEXT>
in his investigation courtappointed examiner 
david i shapiro studied 15 transactions between eastern airlines 
parent texas air corp and nonunion sister continental airlines 
in 12 of the 15 cases shapiro concluded that texas air 
shortchanged eastern by buying its assets at unfairly low prices 
he found most notably that texas air owes eastern 150 million 
to 250 million for the transfer of the system one computer 
reservation system and 61 million for texas airs acquisition of 
eastern in november 1986 
among the other transactions studied were 
a 16 million texas air debt to eastern stemming mostly from 
legal fees and investment banking fees 
management fees paid by eastern to texas air 
transfers of aircraft from eastern to continental 
notes issued by nowdefunct people express airlines which texas 
air sold to eastern 
texas airs fuel management arrangement with eastern 
strike contingency fees paid by eastern to continental 
a 40 million loan from eastern to continental 
easterns payment of cash dividends on preferred stock 
guaranteed by texas air 
</TEXT>
